title: Pennsylvania Voters Absorb an Unusual Debate: ‘I Felt Sorry for Fetterman’
description: In interviews, Democrats and Republicans had a range of reactions to the state’s Senate debate, including alarm, protectiveness, empathy and worry about the political implications.
dc:creator: Katie Glueck and Alyce McFadden

media:content.media:credit: Amanda Mustard for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: “I felt sorry for Fetterman,” said Deb Donahue, 68, a registered Republican and a Mehmet Oz supporter from Camp Hill, Pa. “I think he really struggled a little bit.”
